    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Amos",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 9,
        "summary": "Israel will be sifted among all nations\u2014In the last days, the people of Israel will be gathered again into their own land, and it will become productive.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "I saw the Lord standing upon the altar: and he said, Smite the lintel of the door, that the posts may shake: and cut them in the head, all of them; and I will slay the last of them with the sword: he that fleeth of them shall not flee away, and he that escapeth of them shall not be delivered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 16:9.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 163
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:1; Amos 2:14.",
                        "start": 205,
                        "end": 211
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Though they dig into hell, thence shall mine hand take them; though they climb up to heaven, thence will I bring them down:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 139:8 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And though they hide themselves in the top of Carmel, I will search and take them out thence; and though they be hid from my sight in the bottom of the sea, thence will I command the serpent, and he shall bite them:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 12:10; Alma 12:14.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And though they go into captivity before their enemies, thence will I command the sword, and it shall slay them: and I will set mine eyes upon them for evil, and not for good.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 21:10.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God of hosts is he that toucheth the land, and it shall melt, and all that dwell therein shall mourn: and it shall rise up wholly like a flood; and shall be drowned, as by the flood of Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:25 (23\u201325).",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 8:8.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 182,
                        "end": 184
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is he that buildeth his stories in the heaven, and hath founded his troop in the earth; he that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The Lord is his name.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:33.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 5:8; Moses 2:7 (6\u20137); Abr. 4:9 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 192,
                        "end": 194
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Are ye not as children of the Ethiopians unto me, O children of Israel? saith the Lord. Have not I brought up Israel out of the land of Egypt? and the Philistines from Caphtor, and the Syrians from Kir?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the eyes of the Lord God are upon the sinful kingdom, and I will destroy it from off the face of the earth; saving that I will not utterly destroy the house of Jacob, saith the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 34:15; D&C 1:1; 38:7; 67:2.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 5:33.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 30:11; 2\u00a0Ne. 3:3 (2\u20134); 6:11 (10\u201311); 20:20 (20\u201321).",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 154
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For, lo, I will command, and I will sift the house of Israel among all nations, like as corn is sifted in a sieve, yet shall not the least grain fall upon the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Scattering of.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mal. 3:6.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 149
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All the sinners of my people shall die by the sword, which say, The evil shall not overtake nor prevent us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0confront.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In that day will I raise up the tabernacle of David that is fallen, and close up the breaches thereof; and I will raise up his ruins, and I will build it as in the days of old:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 15:16 (15\u201317). TG\u00a0Temple.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That they may possess the remnant of Edom, and of all the heathen, which are called by my name, saith the Lord that doeth this.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Obad. 1:17; 2\u00a0Ne. 24:2 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 34:5; Jer. 49:17 (7\u201322); Ezek. 25:14 (12\u201314); Obad. 1:18 (8, 18\u201319, 21).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heathen.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, that the plowman shall overtake the reaper, and the treader of grapes him that soweth seed; and the mountains shall drop sweet wine, and all the hills shall melt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 8:22.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 26:3; Morm. 9:2.",
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 200
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will bring again the captivity of my people of Israel, and they shall build the waste cities, and inhabit them; and they shall plant vineyards, and drink the wine thereof; they shall also make gardens, and eat the fruit of them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zeph. 2:7; 3\u00a0Ne. 16:16 (11\u201320).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Gathering of.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 77:15; 84:3 (2\u20135); 101:18; 103:11.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 36:10 (8\u201315).",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will plant them upon their land, and they shall no more be pulled up out of their land which I have given them, saith the Lord thy God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 55:5.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 77:15. TG\u00a0Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 20:29.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}